SQUISH!

90
00:07:12.950 --> 00:07:12.990
SQUISH!

91
00:07:12.990 --> 00:07:13.030
SQUISH!

92
00:07:13.030 --> 00:07:13.070
SQUISH!

93
00:07:13.070 --> 00:07:13.120
SQUISH!

94
00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:13.160
SQUISH!

95
00:07:13.160 --> 00:07:13.200
SQUISH!

96
00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:13.240
SQUISH!

97
00:07:13.240 --> 00:07:13.280
SQUISH!

98
00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:13.320
SQUISH!

99
00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:13.370
SQUISH!

100
00:07:13.370 --> 00:07:13.410
SQUISH!

101
00:07:13.410 --> 00:07:13.450
SQUISH!

102
00:07:13.450 --> 00:07:13.490
SQUISH!

103
00:07:13.490 --> 00:07:13.530
SQUISH!

104
00:07:13.530 --> 00:07:13.570
SQUISH!

105
00:07:13.570 --> 00:07:13.620
SQUISH!

106
00:07:13.620 --> 00:07:13.660
SQUISH!

107
00:07:13.660 --> 00:07:13.700
SQUISH!

108
00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:16.160
He got run over!

109
00:07:18.640 --> 00:07:23.320
Oh, there there, Pez.
It was a little loud back there, right?

110
00:07:33.110 --> 00:07:34.630
He's still there...

111
00:07:37.620 --> 00:07:41.050
Who is that guy? Is he a pervert?

112
00:07:47.420 --> 00:07:50.140
Huh? What's the matter, Pez?

113
00:07:54.050 --> 00:07:57.110
It looks like she's happy.

114
00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:05.630
We need to sail
toward the southeastern sea, Bege!

115
00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:06.870
Okay...

116
00:08:06.870 --> 00:08:11.790
We should just run
through the town to get to the sea.

117
00:08:11.790 --> 00:08:13.280
Pudding!

118
00:08:15.740 --> 00:08:18.750
We'll have to run over
a few chocolate houses.

119
00:08:18.750 --> 00:08:19.670
What?!

120
00:08:20.580 --> 00:08:24.430
That's the only way for us to depart safely!

121
00:08:42.740 --> 00:08:44.690
What a waste.

122
00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:47.240
I'll fix them later.

123
00:08:47.240 --> 00:08:51.280
Houses can be rebuilt.
And so can families.

124
00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:55.290
Yeah. It'd be better
if they didn't break apart, but...

125
00:08:56.360 --> 00:08:59.080
this is my home now.

126
00:08:59.080 --> 00:09:02.000
And you guys are my new family.

127
00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:04.670
Madam!

128
00:09:15.220 --> 00:09:16.800
You bastards!

129
00:09:16.800 --> 00:09:18.780
Stop using the cannon!

130
00:09:18.780 --> 00:09:21.630
You might blow up the cake!

131
00:09:21.630 --> 00:09:24.860
They're gonna get to the sea!
Don't let them escape!

132
00:09:24.860 --> 00:09:27.650
Fleet! Head for the southeastern side
of the island!

133
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.740
We're on our way!

134
00:09:39.020 --> 00:09:42.960
All right! We made it off Cacao Island!

135
00:09:44.370 --> 00:09:45.840
Hooray!

136
00:09:53.540 --> 00:09:57.270
No one can catch up
to this paddle ship now.

137
00:09:57.930 --> 00:10:01.200
Thanks, Bege. You saved us.

138
00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:04.690
I didn't do it for your sake, Black Leg!

139
00:10:07.220 --> 00:10:09.150
Isn't it oddly hot over here?

140
00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:14.720
Father, the sea looks weird-rero !

141
00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:24.270
Fish are floating to the surface!

142
00:10:24.270 --> 00:10:26.440
The sea is so hot that it boiled them?!

143
00:10:26.440 --> 00:10:29.730
With the right amount of salt,
they'd probably taste good...

144
00:10:29.730 --> 00:10:32.150
We're gonna be next, you idiot!

145
00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:36.710
There's only one person capable of this...

146
00:10:36.730 --> 00:10:38.130
Look!

147
00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:42.260
Hot Sea Hell!

148
00:10:42.260 --> 00:10:45.820
With my Heat-Heat Fruit ability,

149
00:10:45.820 --> 00:10:49.190
I will boil you all to death!

150
00:10:51.810 --> 00:10:53.480
It's hot!

151
00:10:53.480 --> 00:10:56.360
It's simmering-rero !

152
00:10:56.360 --> 00:10:58.610
We have a bigger issue to worry about!

153
00:11:00.020 --> 00:11:03.150
This is bad! This'll affect
the temperature of the chocolate!

154
00:11:03.150 --> 00:11:05.580
The whipped cream will melt, too!

155
00:11:05.580 --> 00:11:07.030
That means...

156
00:11:07.030 --> 00:11:11.670
...if nothing is done,
Big Mom's cake will be ruined!

157
00:11:13.370 --> 00:11:16.510
That idiot, what is he thinking?!

158
00:11:16.510 --> 00:11:20.630
Big Mom won't be satisfied with boiled fish!

159
00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:24.390
What happened?!

160
00:11:24.390 --> 00:11:27.020
The heat broke the paddles!

161
00:11:27.020 --> 00:11:30.760
Rero-rero !
Is he planning on sinking our ship?!

162
00:11:30.760 --> 00:11:35.020
Did Minister Oven forget
how important this cake is?!

163
00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:37.200
It's okay...

164
00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:39.240
It's gonna be okay...

165
00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:41.320
Sink...

166
00:11:41.320 --> 00:11:43.700
Sink!

167
00:11:51.570 --> 00:11:56.210
You're acting strange...
Why have you been laughing so much, Pez?

168
00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.590
Who the hell are you?

169
00:12:09.010 --> 00:12:11.600
Minister Oven! Watch out!

170
00:12:13.180 --> 00:12:15.840
Knock it off!

171
00:12:38.520 --> 00:12:41.270
Minister Oven!

172
00:12:42.210 --> 00:12:44.360
What's going on?

173
00:12:44.360 --> 00:12:46.740
Who is that-rero ?

174
00:12:46.740 --> 00:12:49.250
Is he Minister Oven's archnemesis?

175
00:13:02.050 --> 00:13:03.640
Pound!

176
00:13:05.470 --> 00:13:09.270
Y-You're quite tough...

177
00:13:11.890 --> 00:13:13.480
You bastard!

178
00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:18.940
Are you... trying to kill your stepson?!

179
00:13:21.990 --> 00:13:25.780
Father! The water's temperature is falling!

180
00:13:25.780 --> 00:13:30.990
Fold up the paddles!
Let's use this chance to push past the hot water!

181
00:13:30.990 --> 00:13:32.320
Yes, sir!

182
00:13:32.320 --> 00:13:34.290
Let's hurry up and get out of here!

183
00:13:34.290 --> 00:13:36.580
Yes, madam!

184
00:13:41.890 --> 00:13:44.940
To my grandson,
whose name I don't even know...

185
00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:47.560
Are you happy?

186
00:13:48.100 --> 00:13:53.360
Make your mommy and daddy
love you as much as possible...

187
00:13:53.370 --> 00:13:58.190
I couldn't do that for my children...

188
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:02.780
Not yet? Not yet?

189
00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:13.880
Linlin, you gave birth!

190
00:14:13.880 --> 00:14:17.510
Yeah... Lola and Chiffon...

191
00:14:17.510 --> 00:14:19.720
They're twins.

192
00:14:19.720 --> 00:14:23.450
Twins?! I wanna hold them.

193
00:14:23.450 --> 00:14:24.480
What?!

194
00:14:25.300 --> 00:14:29.360
You've already served your purpose.

195
00:14:33.070 --> 00:14:34.770
Go away.

196
00:14:34.770 --> 00:14:36.140
What?

197
00:14:36.140 --> 00:14:37.780
Linlin?

198
00:14:37.780 --> 00:14:39.960
What do you mean?!

199
00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:43.370
I'm their father! We're...

200
00:14:43.370 --> 00:14:47.750
You think they're your family?
Don't overestimate yourself.

201
00:14:56.960 --> 00:14:58.710
Linlin!

202
00:14:59.050 --> 00:15:01.680
Those are my children!

203
00:15:01.680 --> 00:15:03.820
Please!

204
00:15:03.820 --> 00:15:08.730
I wanna hold them at least once!

205
00:15:09.310 --> 00:15:12.980
Linlin!

206
00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:17.520
They're... my children...

207
00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:22.580
That was 26 years ago...

208
00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:27.790
Chiffon...
I'm glad I got to see you at least once.

209
00:15:27.790 --> 00:15:32.170
It seems like you're being chased,

210
00:15:32.910 --> 00:15:36.630
but I'm glad that you look happy...

211
00:15:42.710 --> 00:15:44.800
What's the matter, Pez?

212
00:15:44.800 --> 00:15:50.060
You'll be fine!
We'll be out of this hot sea soon!

213
00:15:50.810 --> 00:15:54.100
There's nothing to be afraid of!

214
00:15:59.350 --> 00:16:01.950
Stop, Mama!

215
00:16:01.950 --> 00:16:03.490
Shut up!

216
00:16:04.610 --> 00:16:08.500
Why did I give birth to twins?!

217
00:16:08.510 --> 00:16:13.710
You're probably a failure just like Lola!

218
00:16:13.710 --> 00:16:16.090
Stop!

219
00:16:16.790 --> 00:16:21.590
Children who are useless to me
aren't part of my family!

220
00:16:25.670 --> 00:16:30.550
Don't you dare show your face around me!

221
00:16:33.010 --> 00:16:37.780
It's going to be all right.
Your Papa and Mama are right here.

222
00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:42.240
I've been worried about you this whole time.

223
00:16:42.730 --> 00:16:45.740
Did you go through any hardships?

224
00:16:46.190 --> 00:16:49.450
Were you ever lonely?

225
00:16:49.450 --> 00:16:55.060
I'm sorry that I couldn't
be there for you on those days...

226
00:16:56.790 --> 00:16:58.670
I know I'm late...

227
00:16:59.620 --> 00:17:02.050
but I wanted to tell you something.

228
00:17:03.040 --> 00:17:04.980
Congratulations...

229
00:17:04.980 --> 00:17:07.600
on your marriage!

230
00:17:07.600 --> 00:17:11.560
Chiffon!

231
00:17:11.560 --> 00:17:12.770
What?!

232
00:17:19.600 --> 00:17:21.100
We escaped-rero !

233
00:17:21.100 --> 00:17:23.530
Keep going at this speed and escape!

234
00:17:26.530 --> 00:17:29.570
The cake barely survived.

235
00:17:31.250 --> 00:17:34.500
Let's hurry up!
We don't have much time!

236
00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:36.460
Let's begin the decorating!

237
00:17:36.460 --> 00:17:38.120
– Okay!
– Yeah!

238
00:17:38.420 --> 00:17:41.420
<b>The Sunny, At Sea</b>

239
00:17:43.630 --> 00:17:45.720
I found you!

240
00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:49.430
Hand over the cake!

241
00:17:54.120 --> 00:17:58.010
B-B... B-B-Big Mom?!

242
00:17:58.010 --> 00:18:00.760
No matter how you look at it,
she's too strong for us!

243
00:18:00.770 --> 00:18:02.430
What should we do?!

244
00:18:04.220 --> 00:18:07.180
Maybe it'd be best to run...

245
00:18:07.510 --> 00:18:11.140
If we stop, that'll be the end!
We need to get away somehow!

246
00:18:13.850 --> 00:18:15.260
Here we go!

247
00:18:15.260 --> 00:18:17.390
I'll go first!

248
00:18:17.390 --> 00:18:19.690
I'll get them!

249
00:18:19.690 --> 00:18:22.070
Huh? Who's our enemy?

250
00:18:22.070 --> 00:18:23.900
It's the Straw Hat crew!

251
00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:28.200
Oh, that's right!
But I don't see a straw hat anywhere!

252
00:18:28.200 --> 00:18:31.330
Excuse me!
Where is the Straw Hat crew?

253
00:18:31.330 --> 00:18:33.000
They went that way!

254
00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:33.990
What?!

255
00:18:33.990 --> 00:18:35.880
Let's go! It's that way!

256
00:18:35.880 --> 00:18:37.670
Thanks for the directions!

257
00:18:37.670 --> 00:18:40.970
Ah! We can't fly that far!

258
00:18:43.850 --> 00:18:45.560
What were they?

259
00:18:45.560 --> 00:18:46.760
I have no idea.

260
00:18:48.920 --> 00:18:50.930
You idiots!

261
00:18:50.930 --> 00:18:54.280
Why are all of the cannonballs so useless?!

262
00:18:54.280 --> 00:18:56.060
What's going on?!

263
00:18:56.060 --> 00:19:00.070
As you know, when Mama's out of control,
they don't listen to us!

264
00:19:00.070 --> 00:19:02.190
Please let me go next!

265
00:19:02.190 --> 00:19:03.780
No, I'm next!

266
00:19:03.780 --> 00:19:09.430
Sir Bavarois! I'll show you that I can do it!

267
00:19:06.290 --> 00:19:10.790
<b>Charlotte Bavarois
26th Son of the Charlotte Family</b>

268
00:19:06.310 --> 00:19:10.790
Bavarois: from "crème bavaroise" or "Bavarian cream"

269
00:19:09.430 --> 00:19:10.790
Damn...

270
00:19:10.790 --> 00:19:16.000
Mama hasn't slowed down,
and we're at full speed, too!

271
00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:17.920
Why can't we catch up to them?!

272
00:19:19.830 --> 00:19:23.720
Well, they have Jinbe,
who knows the seas like the back of his hand.

273
00:19:27.510 --> 00:19:31.470
Sir Bavarois! We just got a call!

274
00:19:32.090 --> 00:19:33.690
Here they come!

275
00:19:34.930 --> 00:19:36.400
Everyone!

276
00:19:36.400 --> 00:19:38.110
What's the matter, Carrot?!

277
00:19:38.110 --> 00:19:40.610
There are a bunch of ships ahead!

278
00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:44.730
What?!

279
00:19:44.730 --> 00:19:47.720
Oh, no! We've been pincered!

280
00:19:52.180 --> 00:19:57.780
Wedding cake!

281
00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:13.880
Gear Third!

282
00:20:20.710 --> 00:20:23.550
We just started up again.
Don't be so erratic.

283
00:20:26.560 --> 00:20:30.870
Even if you had escaped earlier,
I am your opponent.

284
00:20:30.870 --> 00:20:33.350
Nobody would've laughed at you if you did.

285
00:20:34.690 --> 00:20:37.110
So why did you come back?

286
00:20:38.380 --> 00:20:44.040
Did you choose death
over the shame of running away?

287
00:20:44.040 --> 00:20:45.690
"Choose death"?

288
00:20:45.690 --> 00:20:49.540
Or did you notice the difference in our power

289
00:20:49.540 --> 00:20:54.020
and come back here to beg
to become our subordinate?

290
00:20:55.150 --> 00:20:56.690
"Beg"?

291
00:20:59.400 --> 00:21:01.000
Cut the crap...

292
00:21:02.060 --> 00:21:03.210
I...

293
00:21:04.160 --> 00:21:06.380
came here to beat you!

294
00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:17.470
"Came here to beat me"?

295
00:21:17.470 --> 00:21:20.300
That is not...

296
00:21:21.850 --> 00:21:23.850
an option!

297
00:21:38.930 --> 00:21:40.310
Damn...

298
00:21:40.330 --> 00:21:47.130
Before we were able to get Big Mom and the others
off of our tail, our path out of here was blocked!

299
00:21:48.760 --> 00:21:50.730
Sir Bavarois!

300
00:21:50.730 --> 00:21:55.110
Minister Daifuku and his fleet
have arrived just up ahead!

301
00:21:51.990 --> 00:21:55.110
<b>Charlotte Daifuku
3rd Son of the Charlotte Family</b>

302
00:21:55.110 --> 00:21:57.720
And we have reinforcements from behind!

303
00:21:57.720 --> 00:21:58.910
From behind?

304
00:22:00.650 --> 00:22:02.160
That's...

305
00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:04.580
A fleet of reinforcements led by

306
00:22:03.830 --> 00:22:07.580
<b>Sweet Commander
Smoothie
14th Daughter of the Charlotte Family</b>

307
00:22:04.580 --> 00:22:07.580
Sweet Commander Smoothie has arrived!

308
00:22:08.880 --> 00:22:12.420
Not to mention, Commander Smoothie's flag ship has

309
00:22:11.050 --> 00:22:16.430
<b>Citron
15th Daughter of the
Charlotte Family</b>
<b>Cinnamon
16th Daughter of the
Charlotte Family</b>

310
00:22:12.420 --> 00:22:16.430
Mistresses Citron and Mistress Cinnamon on board!

311
00:22:16.430 --> 00:22:18.230
They're going that far?!

312
00:22:19.160 --> 00:22:22.690
But with them, we'll be invincible!

313
00:22:22.690 --> 00:22:25.420
All right. Let's do it, men!

314
00:22:25.420 --> 00:22:27.370
Yeah!

315
00:22:30.480 --> 00:22:35.450
Hey, Brother Peros, why is it taking so long
for you to eliminate one little mouse?

316
00:22:35.450 --> 00:22:38.070
Can I just sink them?

317
00:22:38.070 --> 00:22:41.090
Do whatever you want. Lick...

318
00:22:41.090 --> 00:22:43.800
You guys are so dramatic!

319
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:45.420
It doesn't matter what happens

320
00:22:45.420 --> 00:22:49.800
because Mama is heading to Cacao Island
where Pudding is waiting.

321
00:22:51.170 --> 00:22:54.150
It looks like Mama's getting thinner.

322
00:22:54.150 --> 00:22:55.600
Lick...

323
00:22:57.670 --> 00:23:01.480
Wedding cake!

324
00:23:01.480 --> 00:23:04.940
All ships, prepare to fire!

325
00:23:08.240 --> 00:23:11.690
As soon as their ship comes
within shooting range,

326
00:23:11.690 --> 00:23:13.490
let them have it!

327
00:23:14.270 --> 00:23:15.570
This is bad...

328
00:23:15.570 --> 00:23:18.660
Daifuku's ships are preparing
to fire their cannons!

329
00:23:19.740 --> 00:23:23.180
I don't think we're in their range yet...

330
00:23:23.180 --> 00:23:28.460
Even if we try to dodge,
we're surrounded on all sides.

331
00:23:29.870 --> 00:23:33.840
Jinbe, let's keep advancing
without slowing down!

332
00:23:33.840 --> 00:23:40.180
But we're up against Daifuku's ship...
He controls a jinni and is a formidable opponent!

333
00:23:40.180 --> 00:23:45.390
We have no choice
but to force our way through the front!

334
00:23:45.390 --> 00:23:48.650
Right. Let's prepare ourselves.

335
00:23:48.650 --> 00:23:55.450
I'll start this off by taking a rumble ball!
Get me close enough to jump onto their ship!

336
00:23:55.450 --> 00:23:59.370
Fighting at close range...
It's gonna be tough.

337
00:23:59.370 --> 00:24:00.310
Mm-hm.

338
00:24:00.310 --> 00:24:02.910
Let's go!

339
00:24:04.740 --> 00:24:07.880
They'll be in range soon.

340
00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:10.800
Fire all of our cannonballs at them.

341
00:24:10.800 --> 00:24:12.190
Yeah!

342
00:24:12.190 --> 00:24:14.010
This is our chance!

343
00:24:14.010 --> 00:24:17.010
Hey, use the faceless cannonballs.

344
00:24:17.010 --> 00:24:19.550
– No way!
– Minister Daifuku!

345
00:24:19.550 --> 00:24:20.880
Shut up!

346
00:24:20.880 --> 00:24:23.020
Chobro!

347
00:24:23.020 --> 00:24:24.630
Everyone!

348
00:24:25.240 --> 00:24:28.930
Let me handle Daifuku and the others!

349
00:24:29.760 --> 00:24:32.640
I'll definitely be useful!

350
00:24:32.640 --> 00:24:34.060
Carrot?!

351
00:24:36.310 --> 00:24:38.190
Because...

352
00:24:39.140 --> 00:24:41.900
tonight's a full moon...

353
00:24:42.520 --> 00:24:48.070
Don't tell me... Sulong?!
Are you trained for it?!
"Sulong": moon lion

354
00:24:48.070 --> 00:24:52.870
Don't worry... Pedro trained me.

355
00:24:54.120 --> 00:24:56.930
I know what Pedro would say right now...

356
00:24:57.660 --> 00:25:00.250
"Leave it to me."

357
00:25:00.250 --> 00:25:02.800
If Carrot is going,
I'm going with her!

358
00:25:02.800 --> 00:25:06.250
Leave it to me, Chobro!

359
00:25:07.090 --> 00:25:10.140
I'm still a musketeer, after all!

360
00:25:11.240 --> 00:25:12.720
Everyone, man the cannons!

361
00:25:12.720 --> 00:25:15.690
We'll shoot salvos and sink it quickly!

362
00:25:15.690 --> 00:25:18.520
Wait for my cue!

363
00:25:20.640 --> 00:25:22.900
What do you mean, Pedro?

364
00:25:23.730 --> 00:25:27.030
One day, you'll see how important it was

365
00:25:27.030 --> 00:25:31.910
to allow Luffy and the others to set sail!

366
00:25:35.330 --> 00:25:36.670
I'll fight...

367
00:25:36.670 --> 00:25:38.720
for your share as well...

368
00:25:40.350 --> 00:25:42.150
Pedro!

369
00:26:02.470 --> 00:26:03.800
What is that?

370
00:27:05.170 --> 00:27:08.830
Her eyes are red...
She looks like a different person...

371
00:27:08.830 --> 00:27:12.310
Carrot... She's so beautiful...

372
00:27:12.310 --> 00:27:15.270
How mystical...

373
00:27:15.270 --> 00:27:18.450
Oh, she looks pretty amazing...

374
00:27:18.450 --> 00:27:21.390
I'd like to see her panties...

375
00:27:21.390 --> 00:27:26.070
Is that what Duke Inuarashi was talking about?

376
00:27:26.490 --> 00:27:28.880
But after that battle,

377
00:27:28.880 --> 00:27:35.540
this was the result we had against Jack's squad,
a subset of Kaido's army.

378
00:27:35.540 --> 00:27:41.420
But we won't let that happen again!
We will not repeat the same mistake!

379
00:27:41.420 --> 00:27:43.470
We have our trump card.

380
00:27:43.470 --> 00:27:49.510
If we fight them again,
we'll show them the true power of the minks!

381
00:27:49.510 --> 00:27:54.260
This must be the trump card
he was talking about...

382
00:27:54.260 --> 00:27:56.470
The minks'...

383
00:27:56.470 --> 00:27:58.390
true power!

384
00:28:12.900 --> 00:28:16.160
D-Don't tell me that's...

385
00:28:16.160 --> 00:28:18.500
This is bad, Minister Daifuku!

386
00:28:18.500 --> 00:28:23.290
Tonight's a full moon!
That mink girl that's with the enemy...

387
00:28:23.750 --> 00:28:25.250
turned Sulong!

388
00:28:28.580 --> 00:28:32.550
Guys! Prepare for a close-quarters battle!

389
00:28:33.210 --> 00:28:37.810
If I'm correct, Pedro was from Zou,
the phantom city...

390
00:28:37.820 --> 00:28:41.060
I guess she's from the same place...

391
00:28:48.560 --> 00:28:50.810
She's gonna fall into the sea!

392
00:28:52.560 --> 00:28:54.150
Huh?! What the...

393
00:28:54.150 --> 00:28:57.240
She just flew up from the surface!

394
00:29:00.200 --> 00:29:02.040
Amazing...

395
00:29:02.040 --> 00:29:04.750
That's not all...

396
00:29:06.370 --> 00:29:08.510
Here she comes! Shoot her down!

397
00:29:08.510 --> 00:29:09.290
Yes, sir!

398
00:29:09.290 --> 00:29:10.890
Don't lower your guard!

399
00:29:10.890 --> 00:29:13.230
She's a warrior from Zou!
They're on a different level!

400
00:29:15.960 --> 00:29:17.930
I'll bring her down!

401
00:29:19.340 --> 00:29:21.280
What?!

402
00:29:24.390 --> 00:29:26.610
Don't hold back! Take her out!

403
00:29:40.160 --> 00:29:42.540
Damn! Shoot!

404
00:29:48.410 --> 00:29:50.420
I've got you!

405
00:30:16.020 --> 00:30:17.320
Hey!

406
00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:19.950
What's going on? Chopper!

407
00:30:23.790 --> 00:30:25.420
Damn little rat!

408
00:30:25.420 --> 00:30:30.090
Do you plan on fighting all of the soldiers
in this fleet in order to stop us?!

409
00:30:30.090 --> 00:30:35.510
While you're doing that, your ship will sink!
Stop your futile resistance and–

410
00:30:37.550 --> 00:30:39.010
The helm?!

411
00:30:40.470 --> 00:30:43.230
S-She broke the helm!

412
00:30:43.230 --> 00:30:46.560
Oh, no! Where is our ship heading?!

413
00:30:47.060 --> 00:30:50.690
That little rat!
